ts":{"kind":"markdown","value":"### instance-method `Node::create_publisher`  \nprovided by `<rclcpp/node_impl.hpp>`  \n\n---\n→ `std::shared_ptr<Publisher<Quaternion_<allocator<void>>, allocator<void>>>`  \nParameters:  \n- `const std::string & topic_name (aka const basic_string<char> &)`\n- `const rclcpp::QoS & qos`\n- `const PublisherOptionsWithAllocator<allocator<void>> & options = PublisherOptionsWithAllocator<allocator<void>>()`\n\nCreate and return a Publisher.  \nThe rclcpp::QoS has several convenient constructors, including a conversion constructor for size_t, which mimics older API's that allows just a string and size_t to create a publisher.  \nFor example, all of these cases will work:  \n\\`\\`\\`cpp pub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", 10); // implicitly KeepLast pub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", QoS(10)); // implicitly KeepLast pub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", QoS(KeepLast(10)));  \npub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", QoS(KeepAll()));  \npub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", QoS(1).best_effort().durability_volatile());  \n{ rclcpp::QoS custom_qos(KeepLast(10), rmw_qos_profile_sensor_data);  \npub = node->create_publisher\\<MsgT>(\"chatter\", custom_qos);  \n}  \n\\`\\`\\`  \nThe publisher options may optionally be passed as the third argument for any of the above cases.  \n\\\\param[in] topic_name The topic for this publisher to publish on.  \n\\\\param[in] qos The Quality of Service settings for the publisher.  \n\\\\param[in] options Additional options for the created Publisher.  \n\\\\return Shared pointer to the created publisher.  \n\n---\n```cpp\n// In Node\npublic: template <>\nstd::shared_ptr<Publisher<Quaternion_<allocator<void>>, allocator<void>>>\nNode::create_publisher<\n    geometry_msgs::msg::Quaternion_<std::allocator<void>>, std::allocator<void>,\n    rclcpp::Publisher<geometry_msgs::msg::Quaternion_<std::allocator<void>>>>(\n    const std::string &topic_name, const rclcpp::QoS &qos,\n    const PublisherOptionsWithAllocator<allocator<void>> &options =\n        PublisherOptionsWithAllocator<allocator<void>>())\n```"},"range":{"end":{"character":30,"line":258},"start":{"character":14,"line":258}}}}},{"pid":0,"ph":"i","name":"Log","ts":693401857.58099997,"tid":432740,"args":{"Message":"--> textDocument/clangd.fileStatus"}},{"pid":0,"ph":"i","name":"Log","ts":715824144.90799999,"tid":428318,"args":{"Message":"<-- textDocument/hover(38)"}},{"pid":0,"ph":"X","name":"Queued:Hover","ts":715824205.68599999,"tid":428318,"dur":5.3890000581741333,"args":{"PreambleRequestsNames":[],"RequestsNames":[]}},{"pid":0,"ph":"s","name":"Context crosses threads","ts":715824102.59300005,"tid":428318,"id":77,"cat":"mock_cat"},{"pid":0,"ph":"f","name":"Context crosses threads","ts":715824294.16700006,"tid":432740,"bp":"e","id":77,"cat":"mock_cat"},{"pid":0,"ph":"X","name":"getConfig","ts":715824302.778,"tid":432740,"dur":209.46399998664856,"args":{"path":"/home/sparky/Desktop/SPARX_E/src/motor_commander/include/motor_commander/smc_node.hpp"}},{"pid":0,"ph":"i","name":"Log","ts":715824894.44599998,"tid":432740,"args":{"Message":"getStyle() failed for file /home/sparky/Desktop/SPARX_E/src/motor_commander/include/motor_commander/smc_node.hpp: Error reading /home/sparky/Desktop/SPARX_E/.clang-format: Invalid argument. Fallback is LLVM style."}},{"pid":0,"ph":"i","name":"Log","ts":715824968.09399998,"tid":432740,"args":{"Message":"--> reply:textDocument/hover(38) 0 ms"}},{"pid":0,"ph":"X","name":"Hover","ts":715824279.25999999,"tid":432740,"dur":739.88999998569489,"args":{}},{"pid":0,"ph":"X","name":"textDocument/hover","ts":715824102.59300005,"tid":428318,"dur":125.18499994277954,"args":{"Params":{"position":{"character":21,"line":255},"textDocument":{"uri":"file:///home/sparky/Desktop/SPARX_E/src/motor_commander/include/motor_commander/smc_node.hpp"}},"Reply":null}},{"pid":0,"ph":"i","name":"Log","ts":715825075.63199997,"tid":432740,"args":{"Message":"--